'''Carl Lauten''' is an American [[television director]], associate director and [[yoga]] teacher.
==Career== In 1977, Lauten began his career as a [[stage manager]] on the sitcom ''[[Soap (TV series)|Soap]]''. He has also associate directed for ''[[The Cosby Show]]'', ''[[You Again?]]'', ''[[ALF (TV series)|ALF]]'', ''[[The Mommies (TV series)|The Mommies]]'', ''[[Spin City]]'', ''[[That's So Raven]]'', ''[[Hope & Faith]]'', ''[[Cory in the House]]'' and ''[[Sonny with a Chance]]''. In addition to taking over as head director for the some of aforementioned sitcoms, he also directed episodes of ''[[Taina (TV series)|Taina]]'', ''[[Clarissa Explains It All]]'' and ''[[The Suite Life on Deck]]''.
In 1985, he won a [[Directors Guild of America Award]] for directorial work on ''The Cosby Show''.<ref>[https://www.imdb.com/event/ev0000212/1985]</ref>
Lauten is also yoga instructor and yoga video director.<ref>[http://www.raelpilates.com/dp.asp About The Producer And Director, Rael Pilates.com] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110715145742/http://www.raelpilates.com/dp.asp |date=July 15, 2011 }}</ref><ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=R-kDAAAAMBAJ&pg=PA37&dq=Carl+Lauten&hl=en&ei=xZbtTLLBFoP88AaB2OWVAw&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=1&ved=0CCYQ6AEwAA#v=onepage&q=Carl%20Lauten&f=false Arobic Yogo advertisement from Yoga Journal May-Jun 1992] via Google Books</ref> During the early 2000s, he directed a number of yoga and [[pilates]] videos.<ref>[http://productsearch.barnesandnoble.com/search/results.aspx?store=dvd&CTR=970717&OURL=CastCrew/Carl-Lauten Carl Lauten search] {{dead link|date=August 2017|bot=medic}}{{cbignore|bot=medic}} at [[Barnes & Noble]].com</ref>
