{{Infobox School | name = Zagol Academy | image = | imagesize = | caption = | streetaddress = P.O. Box: 6669 | city = [[Addis Ababa]] | state = | zipcode = | country = {{flagcountry|Ethiopia}} | coordinates = {{Coord|9|1|21.46|N|38|51|34.59|E}} | denomination = | head of school = Elias Lewetegn | staff = | teaching_staff = | ceeb = | avg_class_size = | ratio = | grades = LKG1–8 | campus size = | campus type = | athletics = | conference = | slogan = | motto = | motto_translation = | accreditation = | mascot = | patron = | colors = | yearbook = | publication = | newspaper = | established = 2009 | status = | closed = | enrollment = | enrollment_as_of = | free_label = | free_text = | free_label1 = | free_text1 = | free_label2 = | free_text2 = | free_label3 = | free_text3 = | free_label4 = | free_text4 = | free_label5 = | free_text5 = | footnotes = | picture = | homepage = http://www.zagolacademy.com/ }}
'''Zagol Academy''' is a private educational institution concentrating in both [[English language|English]] and [[Amharic]], located in [[Addis Ababa]], [[Ethiopia]], offering Lower Kindergarten through primary school.
==History== The school was founded in 2009 under the leadership of Elias Lewetegn and Tsegay Denboba. Elias Lewetegn has a master's degree (MSc) in Physics and Math from [[Addis Ababa University]].<ref>[http://www.zagolacademy.com/aboutus.html Zagol Academy: About Us]</ref> His research in renewable energy, particularly solar cells has been published by the international journal ''Renewable Energy''.<ref>[http://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/B6V4S-3XYG515-6/2/9dcdeabc754e52adaf7707b2db3e818al Renewable Energy]</ref> Tsegay Denboba spent eight years in the Ministry of Education as a high school teacher and a Senior Research Expert in Distance Education and 25 years in the Ethiopian Mapping Agency, reaching Head of the Planning Department. He has a BA in Geography from Addis Ababa University's Faculty of Education and an MSc in Research Development Planning from the [[International Institute for Geo-Information Science and Earth Observation]] (ITC) in the Netherlands.<ref>[http://geoinfo.uneca.org/geoinfo/ethiopia/EMA.html Ethiopian Mapping Authority]</ref>
==Campus== Zagol Academy has two campuses, one for Lower KG 1, Lower KG 2 and KG and one for its primary and middle school (grades 1-8). Both campuses are located midway between CMC and Ayat (Meri), near Gift Real-Estate.
==Curriculum== The curriculum of Zagol Academy follows the curriculum established by the Ministry of Education with a focus on English, creative thinking, teamwork and technology.<ref>[http://www.zagolacademy.com/aboutus.html#curriculum Zagol Academy: Curriculum]</ref>
